                       Jerky - Water/Smoker Method

Recipe By     : Richard Langer
Serving Size  : 1    Preparation Time :0:00
Categories    : Bbq List                         Jerky

  Amount  Measure       Ingredient -- Preparation Method
--------  ------------  --------------------------------
   1 1/2  pounds        beef flank steak
     1/4  cup           sugar
   2      teaspoons     paprika
     1/4  cup           non-iodized salt
   2      teaspoons     garlic powder
   2      teaspoons     ground black pepper
   1      teaspoon      ginger

Fire up your smoker and start settling the coals in for a long slow smoke before starting the rub.

Pat the meat dry with a paper towel and slice it, with the blade of the knife 30F to the horizontal, across the grain, creating strips 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.

In a small mixing bowl, blend together the sugar, salt, paprika, garlic powder, pepper and ginger.  Rub this mixture into the meat, putting the spiced strips on the grill, but don't fill the water pan.  Give the jerky 3 to 5 hours of smoke at 130 to 180F.  propping the lid open a crack if the temperature threatens to rise disastrously beyond the desired range.

When the strips are chewy-crisp, remove them from the heat, let cool, and store individually in plastic wrap.  Refrigerate to store longer than a few days.

Source: "Where There's Smoke, There's Flavor" by Richard Langer

